of hospitals, and ventilated them, and now comes blowing hither as innocent as 
fleeces. Out upon it!—it’s tainted. Were I the wind, I’d blow no more on 
such a wicked, miserable world. I’d crawl somewhere to a cave, and slink 
there. And yet, ’tis a noble and heroic thing, the wind! who ever conquered 
it? In every fight it has the last and bitterest blow. Run tilting at it, and 
